<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="ja">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>{{.ProjectName}}</title>
<style>
  /* The HUD is a TRANSPARENT overlay composited on top of your C++ drawing.
     Keep the background transparent so whatever you draw in on_draw() (the
     native render layer) shows through.

     Everything below is plain HTML/CSS. The values come from C++ via the
     declarative binder — no JavaScript glue. You write data-m-* attributes,
     C++ pushes named state (see src/main.cpp: w.set("view.x", ...)), and the
     binder keeps the DOM in sync. Richer patterns (lists, conditionals,
     formatting) live in the `clicker` and `shooter` templates and ADR 0007. */
  html, body {
    margin: 0;
    height: 100%;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: transparent;          /* lets the C++ render layer show */
    pointer-events: none;             /* clicks fall through to the game */
    font-family: "Noto Sans JP", "Hiragino Sans", "Yu Gothic", system-ui, sans-serif;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .hud {
    position: absolute;
    top: 16px;
    left: 16px;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    background: rgba(10, 12, 20, 0.55);
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
  .moving {
    color: #74d8f0;
    font-size: 15px;
  }
  .hint {
    position: absolute;
    left: 16px;
    bottom: 14px;
    font-size: 15px;
    opacity: 0.7;
    text-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
  <!-- data-m-tpl interpolates pushed values; data-m-show toggles on truthiness.
       Both are driven entirely from C++ — there is no <script> of your own. -->
  <div class="hud">
    <div data-m-tpl="位置  X {view.x}   Y {view.y}">位置  X 640   Y 360</div>
    <div class="moving" data-m-show="view.moving">— 移動中 —</div>
  </div>

  <div class="hint">矢印キーで移動 · ESC で終了 · この HUD は JavaScript ゼロ (data-m-*)</div>

  <!-- The binder runtime. `mitiru build` copies mitiru_runtime/* next to this
       file automatically — you do not commit or edit these. -->
  <script src="mitiru_runtime/mitiru_cef_state.js"></script>
  <script src="mitiru_runtime/mitiru_bind.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
